FBIS4-7195 "dreas082_a_94020" FBIS-EAS-94-082 Daily Report 28 Apr 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Biographical Sketches of New Cabinet Members Biographical Sketches of New Cabinet Members Telecommunications Minister Hikasa OW2804080994 Tokyo KYODO in English 0724 GMT 28 Apr 94 OW2804080994 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Tokyo, April 28 KYODO -- New Posts and Telecommunications Minister Katsuyuki Hikasa is one of the main policy experts in Buddhist-backed Komeito [Clean Government Party], an influential party in the coalition government. Hikasa, 48, Komeito's Policy Board chairman, has never failed to peruse the bulk of budget documents every year ever since the party was in the opposition camp until last August. He played an active role in the ruling parties to draft 1994 budget bills and a tax reform plan. Hikasa replaced Takenori Kanzaki, his comrade in Komeito. Hikasa is said to be friendly and is well versed in ancient arts and ceramics. He has been elected a House of Representatives legislator four times from the No. 1 constituency in Okayama Prefecture.
